The paper discusses the adversarial robustness of graph neural networks (GNNs) and proposes a novel gradient-based attack method and an optimization-based adversarial training method. This work involves machine learning and optimization techniques, which are commonly found in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
